rsity </i>podcast. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s as simple as that.=E2=80=9D<br/><b=
r/>On the show, McManus recounted the story behind CBS Sports=E2=80=99 bid =
to
swipe the AFC package from NBC in 1998, which he said was truly one of the =
happiest moments in his life=E2=80=94wedding, kids=E2=80=99 births, and all=
 that aside, yada yada. Here=E2=80=99s Sean in his own words: =E2=80=9CAll =
I thought about when I got the job was, <i>What can we do to get the NFL ba=
ck?</i> We focused on the AFC package and convinced the NFL to do that deal=
 first. We knew that NBC was targeting <i>Monday Night Football</i>. We gav=
e them a huge number=E2=80=94$500 million=E2=80=94and they accepted our off=
er on a Friday afternoon. NBC had the right to match until 9 a.m. Monday mo=
rning. Every time my phone rang during the weekend, I would jump 100 feet a=
nd think, oh my God, it=E2=80=99s <b>Paul Tagliabue</b>, the commissioner, =
calling to tell me that NBC had matched=E2=80=94which would have been perso=
nally and professionally just devastating. We get to Monday morning, and Pa=
ul Tagliabue calls and says, =E2=80=99NBC didn=E2=80=99t match.=E2=80=99 We=
ll, at the last minute, ABC decided they were going to re-up <i>Monday Nigh=
t
Football</i>, and all of a sudden NBC said they wanted to bid on the AFC pa=
ckage. And the NFL told them that that deal had already been done.=E2=80=9D=
<br/><br/>McManus continued: =E2=80=9CTo give you an idea of how big this w=
as for CBS, when I told our head of communications, <b>LeslieAnne Wade</b>,=
 she burst into hysterical tears. She was so unbelievably moved. Word start=
ed spreading in the halls of CBS Sports and you could hear screams. Normall=
y, people don=E2=80=99t just run into the president=E2=80=99s office withou=
t being announced. That day, they ran into my office and hugged me. =E2=80=
=A6 I called my parents, they couldn=E2=80=99t believe it. The industry cou=
ldn=E2=80=99t believe it. A year later, we were the number one network agai=
n.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/></li><li><i>Postseason streaming gripes</i>: I saw com=
plaints online that the S.E.C., A.C.C., and Big 12 championship football ga=
mes were not available on ESPN+ over the weekend. One social media user <u>=
